09/02/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- KFOR plans to conduct a military drill between February 18th and February 22nd, with more than 17,000 soldiers expected to take part. The exercise will test the sustainability and capabilities of NATO units deployed in Kosovo and their readiness to conduct operations involving the whole province. The drill is also aimed at boosting co-operation between the international and local police forces, as well as with the EU Planning Team for Kosovo, which is working on an EU crisis management procedure regarding the rule of law. (Makfax - 08/02/07) 
